    think='Now I have a very comprehensive understanding of the PR. Let me updat
e my todo list and start writing the review report.\n\nKey observations:\n\n**Bl
ocking Issues:**\n1. **MatchingGateway uses manual jwt.verify instead of JwtServ
ice** - This violates `nestjs.md` Gateway authentication section: "JWT 认证必须
复用 JwtService，禁止在 Gateway 中直接调用 jwt.verify(token, secret) 手动校验". 
The MatchingGateway at line 53 directly calls `jwt.verify(token, jwtConfig.secre
t)` instead of injecting `JwtService`. This is a Blocking issue because it\'s a 
security/auth consistency violation explicitly called out in the project standar
ds.\n\n2. **ImBloc registered as LazySingleton instead of Factory** - In `di.dar
t`, `ImBloc` is registered as `registerLazySingleton`. According to `flutter.md`
BLoC registration guidelines, global shared Blocs like `ImBloc` should be regist
ered at app level (which is correct), BUT using `registerLazySingleton` means th
e same instance is reused forever. The issue is that `ImBloc` maintains internal
mutable state (`_messages`, `_pendingMessages`, `_currentConversationId`). If th
e user logs out and logs in as a different user, the same `ImBloc` instance with
old state would be reused. Typically Blocs should be `registerFactory` or at lea
st there\'s a concern here. Wait, looking more carefully at `flutter.md`: it say
s "全局共享（如 `AuthBloc`、`ImBloc`）注册位置：app.dart 的 MultiBlocProvider...
". It doesn\'t explicitly say singleton vs factory. But in the example, it shows
`BlocProvider(create: (_) => getIt<ImBloc>())`. If `getIt<ImBloc>()` returns a l
azy singleton, then yes it\'s shared globally. This is actually intentional for 
Socket connection. But the issue is that when user logs out, the Bloc is not rec
reated on next login. Looking at the code, `ImBloc.close()` disconnects socket b
ut doesn\'t clear message caches. When a new user logs in, the old messages from
previous user would still be there. This is a **Blocking** data privacy issue.\n
\n3. **MatchingGateway.afterInit uses runtime hack for CORS** - `nestjs.md` expl
icitly prohibits this: "CORS 配置禁止运行时修改内部引擎对象：通过 afterInit 将 s
erver 强转为 unknown 再修改 engine.opts.cors 属于非公开 API 的 hack". The Matchi
ngGateway.afterInit at lines 32-42 does exactly this. This is a Blocking issue p
er project standards.\n\n**Major Issues:**\n4. **ImBloc auto-reads incoming mess
ages without user opening conversation** - In `_onReceiveMessage`, when a messag
e is received for the current conversation, it automatically calls `_socketClien
t?.markAsRead()`. This violates the PRD requirement for read receipts: "When Bob
opens the conversation, all unread messages from Alice should be marked as read"
. Auto-marking as read on receive means the sender immediately sees "read" statu
s even if the receiver hasn\'t actually opened/read the message. This is a Major
UX issue.\n\n5. **`conversation:updated` event handling in ImBloc causes full re
load** - `_onConversationUpdated` simply calls `add(const LoadConversations())`.
This means every time any conversation gets a new message, the entire conversati
on list is re-fetched from the API. For a high-frequency chat app, this is very 
inefficient. The PRD says "Alice\'s conversation list should update within 1 sec
ond" but doesn\'t specify it must be a full API reload. The event payload alread
y contains `last_message` info, so the Bloc could update the specific conversati
on in-place.\n\n6. **BDD tests for real-time message delivery don\'t actually te
st Socket.io** - The `im_real_time_message_delivery.steps.js` tests use HTTP POS
T to `/messages` and just verify the HTTP response. They don\'t actually test th
e Socket.io real-time delivery path (no socket client connection, no `message:re
ceive` event verification). This is a Major testing gap because the PRD explicit
ly requires "Bob should receive the message within 1 second" via Socket.io.\n\n7
. **BDD test for offline push notification has empty assertion** - Line 86: `ass
ert.ok(true);` - The push notification step has a vacuous assertion. This is a M
ajor issue per `testing.md`: "Step Definition 禁止空实现".\n\n8. **ImService.get
Conversations uses raw SQL with potential type safety issues** - The native SQL 
query uses `(?)` placeholder with an array `[conversationIds]`. In mysql2, passi
ng an array as a single parameter won\'t expand to `IN (...)` correctly. This co
uld cause a SQL error when there are multiple conversation IDs. Wait, looking at
the code: `await this.dataSource.query(..., [conversationIds])` where `conversat
ionIds` is an array of strings. In mysql2, if you pass an array as a parameter, 
it might be serialized as a JSON string or comma-separated string, but TypeORM\'
s `query()` method may or may not handle array expansion for `?` placeholders. T
his is risky. However, TypeORM\'s `query()` might handle it. Let me not flag thi
s as blocking without more evidence.\n\nActually wait, looking at `nestjs.md`: "
原生 SQL 必须使用 `?` 位置参数，禁止 `:paramName`". It does use `?`. But the arr
ay expansion issue is real. Let me check if there\'s evidence of it not working.
.. I don\'t have runtime evidence so I won\'t flag it as blocking.\n\n9. **Messa
geDto schema in OpenAPI missing `client_message_id` in required fields** - Looki
ng at `im.yaml`, `MessageDto` has `client_message_id` as optional (not in `requi
red`), but the `SendMessageDto` in NestJS has it as optional too. That\'s consis
tent.\n\n10. **ImService.sendMessage has DTO required `content` but ValidateIf o
n MaxLength** - The `SendMessageDto` has `content!: string` with `@ValidateIf((o
) => o.type === "text") @IsString() @MaxLength(500)`. But wait - `content` is NO
T marked as `@IsOptional()`, so ValidationPipe will require it for ALL message t
ypes, including `image`. An image message might not have `content` (or might hav
e an empty URL). According to `nestjs.md` DTO conditional validation section, th
is could be problematic. If someone sends an image message with empty content, i
t would fail validation. This is a Major issue.\n\n11. **SwChatInputBar missing 
